This paper deals with Positive Unlabeled (PU) learning for image classification, which is a problem commonly addressed in the machine learning community. The proposed approach uses Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs), which are widely used in the subfield of deep learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper also discusses the architecture and loss function of the proposed model, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.CL (Computation and Language).
